                "invention-title": [
                    "Method for electrochemically separating and recovering cadmium from solution",
                    "一种从溶液中电化学分离及回收镉的方法"
                ]
            },
            "abstract": [
                {
                    "p": "The invention relates to a method for electrochemically separating and recovering cadmium from a solution, and belongs to the field of heavy metal separation. The preparation method comprises the following specific steps: placing cathodes and anodes with different areas in a cadmium-containing solution, and communicating the cathodes and anodes to form an electrochemical path; dissolving the anode without adding any power supply and controlling the reaction temperature to obtain sponge cadmium at the anode; and after the reaction is finished, washing and separating anode sediments. The solution cadmium separation and recovery method provided by the invention has the advantages of simple process, high separation efficiency, cleanness, low energy consumption and easiness in industrial production, deposited cadmium grows in a dendritic crystal form, so that the anode is prevented from being wrapped by the deposited cadmium, and the deposition efficiency of the cadmium is also improved due to exposure of the anode. Sponge cadmium with relatively high purity can be obtained; and byproducts of electric energy and hydrogen in the reaction process are clean energy, so that the method is good in environmental protection property and wide in application space."
                },
                {
                    "p": "本发明涉及一种从溶液中电化学分离及回收镉的方法，属于重金属分离领域。具体制备步骤包括，将不同面积的阴阳极置于含镉溶液中，连通阴阳极构成电化学通路；不外加任何电源并控制反应温度使阳极溶解，在阳极得到海绵镉；反应结束后，对阳极沉积物进行洗涤分离。本发明提供了一种具有工艺简单、分离效率高、清洁、能耗低，且易于工业化生产的溶液镉分离及回收方法，由于沉积的镉呈枝晶生长，避免了沉积镉对阳极的包裹，而阳极的裸露也提高了镉的沉积效率。可获得纯度较高的海绵镉；反应过程副产的电能和氢气均为清洁能源，环保性好，拥有广阔的应用空间。"
                }
            ]
        }
